gomodel:SYNGO_1657  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Neuroglycan C immunoractivity is localized in Purkinje cell synapses of the five-day old cerebellum. \"The cell membrane and the membranes of endoplasmic reticula were not immunostained in the other types of cell, such as granule cells and Bergmann glial cells.\". p. 341 (statement of the authors). Accordingly, the protein must be postsynaptic.\n\n24/11/2017 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: \"Localization of NGC in the Purkinje cells of the five-day-old and adult mice.\". p. 341, figure legend" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099055 replaced by GO:0045211" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1657" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
